<p>
<lb n="1"/><hi rend="grantha">svasti śrī</hi>
<lb n="2"/>maturai ko
<lb n="3"/>ṇṭa koppa
<lb n="4"/>rakecaripaṉmaṟ
<lb n="5"/>ku yāṇṭu 19 Ā
<lb n="6"/>vatu kuṉṟakkūṟṟattu
<lb n="7"/><hi rend="grantha">brahmade</hi>yam ciṟu
<lb n="8"/><note>From this line onwards, and up to line 17 included, the left side pilaster is inscribed.</note> paḻuvūrt ti <g type="kaḻañcu"/> ruvālantuṟai <hi rend="grantha">mahā</hi>
<lb n="9"/><hi rend="grantha">de</hi>varkku O <g type="kaḻañcu"/> ru nonttāviḷakku
<lb n="10"/>ca<hi rend="grantha">ndrādi</hi>val <g type="kaḻañcu"/> Erippatār viṟai
<lb n="11"/>kkūṟṟattu U <g type="kaḻañcu"/> ppaḷappāṭi taṇṭi
<lb n="12"/>A<unclear>ṭi</unclear>kaḷār <g type="kaḻañcu"/> Ivvūr<hi rend="grantha">sabhai</hi>yyā
<lb n="13"/>r vacam kuṭu <g type="kaḻañcu"/> tta cāvāmuvāppe
<lb n="14"/>rāṭu 90 <g type="kaḻañcu"/> Ittoṇṇūṟu Ā
<lb n="15"/>ṭṭālum ni <g type="kaḻañcu"/> catam nārāyattu
<lb n="16"/>Uḻakku ne <g type="kaḻañcu"/> y Aṭuvār Ānār
<lb n="17"/>Icciṟupa <g type="kaḻañcu"/> ḻuvūr<hi rend="grantha">sabhai</hi>yyā
<lb n="18"/>r <unclear>I</unclear>tu pa<unclear>ṉ</unclear><hi rend="grantha">māhe</hi>
<lb n="19"/><hi rend="grantha">śvara rakṣai</hi> ||
</p>

</div>

<div type="apparatus">

</div>

<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">

<p>Fortune! Prosperity! This is the 19th year of Kōpparakesarivarman who has taken Madurai. To Mahādeva of Tiruvalāntuṟai of Ciṟupaḻuvūr, a <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign> of Kuṉṟakkūṟṟam, for a perpetual lamp (<foreign>oru nonttāviḷakku</foreign> &gt; <foreign>oru nontāviḷakku</foreign>) to burn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>erippatār</foreign></supplied> as long as the sun and the moon endure (<foreign>candrādival </foreign>&gt; <foreign>candrāditaval</foreign>), Taṇṭi Aṭikaḷ of Uppaḷappāṭi of Viṟaikkūṟṟam gave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kuṭutta</foreign></supplied> 90 undying and non-ageing <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>cāvāmūvā</foreign></supplied> great goats <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>perāṭu</foreign></supplied> in the care of <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vacam</foreign></supplied> those of the Sabhā <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>sabhaiyyār</foreign></supplied>; those of the Sabhā <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>sabhaiyyār</foreign></supplied> of this Ciṟupaḻuvūr will supply <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>aṭuvār ānār</foreign></supplied> an <foreign>uḻakku</foreign> of <foreign>ghee</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ney</foreign></supplied> by the <foreign>nārāyam</foreign> [measure] every day <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nicatam</foreign></supplied> with all these ninety <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ittoṇṇūṟu</foreign></supplied> goats <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>āṭṭālum</foreign></supplied>. This is under the protection of the Paṉmāheśvaras. </p></div>

